replies.bodyText:
If the intention is to have LimitedRole#names to report creator's roles instead of the synthetic roles

This is the intention indeed.

I wonder whether it would be better to just override Role#names instead of changing it here.

That was my first intention as well, but here's how the limited role creation looked like:
    public static LimitedRole createLimitedRole(Role fromRole, Role limitedByRole) {
        Objects.requireNonNull(limitedByRole, "limited by role is required to create limited role");
        return new LimitedRole(limitedByRole.names(), fromRole.cluster(), fromRole.indices(), fromRole.application(),
                fromRole.runAs(), limitedByRole);
    }

After I raised the PR I realised I need to invert the conjunctions as you've described and maybe forgot to push that.
Overriding LimitedRole#names is another option. I can make that work.

@ywangd I went with your suggestion of:

It might be simpler to just override the names method unless there is some concern that I am missing

In a seeparate PR #59041 .

